22/03/2007
DIYARBAKIR, Turkey -- Police reportedly detained 32 people in Diyarbakir and 13 others in Izmir, as celebrations of the Kurdish religious holiday Nevruz began on Wednesday (March 21st). According to the pro-Kurdish Democratic Society Party, about 100 participants in Nevruz rallies were rounded up. Authorities say the demonstrators threw rocks and shouted slogans in support of Abdullah Ocalan, the jailed leader of the terrorist organisation Kurdistan Workers' Party. (Focus, Zaman - 22/03/07; AFP, NTV, DHA - 21/03/07) 
